text:
I appreciate the fact you guys are able to calmly engage with this stuff without overwhelming moral panic. 
Benjamin seems cool, and his Hobbes-framing is very relevant. (But sustainable M-C-M' is why massive meteorite collisions are sub-optimal.)
Primary topic that needs conversational attention is The Numogram. That's the highest level of transcendental cartography, where all your theoretical questions find any resolution they are capable of meeting. ...

... An attempt to hold me to the "what about capitalist reterritorialization?" question would also be understandable. How is the process not captured by sameness? is also exactly what The Numogram maps, which is Keiji Nishitani's 'What is Religion?' question.

... But Nishitani (and the Kyoto School generally) lacks The Numogram, and so ends up slithering about in words without ultimate sense. 
There's no logic beyond explicated Decimal Revelation, in which there are irreducibly many.

... Eventually the electronics industry will work this out, and then Integrated Doomcrypt-Brain Circuits will complete technological history. Precise production specifications still incoming. Revelation discusses this.
Independence is the lodestone.
No. I've only read one hideous little book of his, relatively recently.
... Very worst type of sanctimonious French communist moralizing.
It really was Boomer tyranny all along.
Sounds awesome.
FFS.
In a rough world, seeking dominance through brand management (rather than industrial capability) is a dysfunctionally high-trust strategy.
Starmer bravely accepting that his participation in Ass Jihad wasn't actually straight sex.

Lots of great stuff in the second half of this about parasitism, wokeness, indiscriminate empathy, institutional decay, and the Fall, though.

Seeing Boomer portfolios in chaos has lifted his popularity with every other generation by ~5%.

Not obnoxious about it though, so you're forgiven.
Ron totally refuses to accept that. Dreams of time-traveling to defeat teenage Hitler in an antisemitic rap-battle. His whole site is about this.

... The fact that the Ashkenazim are in the end more offended by the idea that the goyim might out-perform them in antisemitism than they are by antisemitism is why you have to love them (Anglos, at least).

... This tier of vaguely rightist commentary could hideously cannibalize itself without much risk of serious damage IMHO.

The "Better everything burns than continue deferring to you mofos" right cannot but despise the "Maybe we could shunt things a little bit in our direction" 'right' even when there's a momentary tactical alignment. I doubt the latter yet quite gets who is enabling things for them.
I was going along with you up to the last sentence.
... Politics has its deep rules, and since they seem difficult to side-step, it might be best to grasp what they are. Realistically capturing the Zoomer trajectory is a good start.
Adoring Zoomers right now in the way I adore unaligned AI and reckless nuclear proliferation. ...
